# Walkthrough — GoLive Phase 14: We Are Live! 🔴

## Summary
The platform now supports (simulated) live streaming with real-time chat. This was the final major feature to achieve parity with platforms like Twitch/YouTube Live.

---

## Changes Made

### 1. Live Streaming Infrastructure
- **Schema**: Added `is_live` column to videos and a dedicated `live_chat_messages` table.
- **Go Live Studio**: New page at `/studio/golive` allows users to start a broadcast.
- **Live Watch Page**: `/live/[id]` features a dedicated layout with a theater-mode player and a real-time chat sidebar.

### 2. Real-time Features
- **Chat**: Powered by Supabase Realtime. Messages appear instantly for all viewers without refreshing.
- **Sidebar Updates**: The "Live Channels" section in the sidebar now updates in real-time as users go live.

## Verification
- **Run SQL**: You MUST run [setup-live-streaming.sql](file:///C:/GoLive/setup-live-streaming.sql) in Supabase.
- **Test Flow**:
    1.  Go to `/studio` -> Click "Go Live".
    2.  Enter title, Start Stream.
    3.  You are redirected to the Live page.
    4.  Open the app in another tab (incognito) to chat and see yourself in the sidebar.
